  org.sbml.squeezer.KineticLawGenerator

public class KineticLawGenerator

Constructor Detail

KineticLawGenerator

public KineticLawGenerator(Model model)
                    throws ClassNotFoundException
Takes a Model as input, creates a copy of the Model, updates the enzymatic catalysis information using the given settings and creates kinetic laws for each reaction in the model copy. The original Model remains unchanged. Note that this constructor only initializes the KineticLawGenerator. The actual kinetic equations are created by calling generateLaws(). In order to synchronize the sub-model with the original Model, call storeKineticLaws().

Parameters:
model - for whose reactions kinetic equations are to be created.
Throws:
ClassNotFoundException - happens if the preferences contain references to classes of kinetic equations that do not exist.

createKineticLaw

public BasicKineticLaw createKineticLaw(Reaction r,
                                        Class<?> kineticsClass,
                                        boolean reversibility,
                                        TypeStandardVersion version,
                                        UnitConsistencyType consistency,
                                        double defaultNewParamVal)
                                 throws Throwable
Creates a kinetic law for the given reaction, which can be assigned to the given reaction.

Parameters:
r - The reaction for which a kinetic law is to be created.
kineticsClass - a Class object that is derived from BasicKineticLaw.
reversibility - If true this reaction will be set to reversible and the kinetic equation will be created accordingly. If this parameter is false, the reversibility property of this reaction will not be changed.
version -
consistency -
defaultNewParamVal -
Returns:
A kinetic law for the given reaction.
Throws:
Throwable

storeKineticLaw

public Reaction storeKineticLaw(KineticLaw kineticLaw)
This method stores a KineticLaw for the given Reaction in the currently selected Model given by the user. The KineticLaw is passed to this method. A boolean variable tells this method weather the formula is for a reversible or for an irreversible Reaction (in the user's Preferences). Afterwards all parameters within this KineticLaw are also stored in the given Model. There is no need to call the #storeParamters(Reaction) method.

Parameters:
kineticLaw - A string with the formula to be assigned to the given reaction.
l -

updateEnzymeCatalysis

public void updateEnzymeCatalysis()
Sets the SBO annotation of modifiers to more precise values in the local mini copy of the model. Updates the minimal model so that all possible enzymes are marked as enzymatic catalyst.
